; ============================
; Arglax's Engine.ini SAMPLE Configuration Overview
; ============================

; This configuration file has been customized for ultra-high quality, high performance and stability on Android devices using Unreal Engine.
; It includes multithreading optimizations, memory management, streaming performance, shader compilation behavior,
; garbage collection, AI enhancements, and more. Each section influences specific subsystems of the engine.
; Uses Poco X6 Pro 5G as the basis model.
; This config file is aided by ChatGPT and GPT-derivative: Unreal Engine 4 Expert and are fully tested and tweaked by Arglax.

; DISCLAIMER: This configuration is intended solely to enhance the visual quality and performance of Wuthering Waves. While it has been tested and is considered safe, by using this configuration, you acknowledge that I am not responsible for any potential issues that may arise—including but not limited to crashes, data loss, hardware damage, or account penalties. Use at your own discretion.
; This config, when used as is, may NOT work

; ============================
; CATEGORY OVERVIEW
; ============================

; [Core.System]                    			  	  - Sets engine and plugin content paths and startup flags.
; [Physics]                        			  	  - Controls physics threading, substepping, ragdolls.
; [SystemSettings]                    				  - Core rendering, quality, and graphical CVars (applied at runtime).
; [SystemSettingsEditor]            				  - Editor-specific rendering and performance CVars.
; [/Script/Engine.StreamingSettings]				  - Controls streaming priorities, time limits, and other engine-level overrides.
; [TextureStreaming]                				  - Additional controls for texture streaming pool size, mip bias, etc.
; [DevOptions.Shaders]            				  - Shader compiler options (DXC, precompilation).
; [ShaderPipelineCache.CacheFile]  				  - (optional) Shader pipeline cache configuration.
; [SystemSettings.ShaderPipelineCache] 			          - Handles runtime shader cache prewarming.
; [UnrealEd.EditorEngine]           				  - Editor behavior overrides.
; [/Script/Engine.Engine]           				  - Engine-wide rendering and gameplay system flags.
; [/Script/Engine.GarbageCollectionSettings] 			  - Memory cleanup and GC tuning.
; [/Script/AndroidRuntimeSettings.AndroidRuntimeSettings] 	  - Android-only packaging and runtime behavior.
; [CrashReportClient]              				  - Crash report behavior and user data toggles.
; [DerivedDataBackendGraph]        				  - Asset data cache and disk usage control.
; [VertexCompress]                 				  - Custom compression behavior for mesh vertex data.
; [NPCs]                           				  - Custom category for AI update threading, optimizations.
; [Startup]                        				  - Launch flags and behavior overrides (e.g., threading, GPU crash control).
; [Log]                            				  - Controls logging verbosity globally or per-subsystem.
; [StudioTelemetry.Log]            				  - (Optional) Custom telemetry tagging or suppression.


